      "type": "Video",
      "product_type": "clips",
      "caption": "No one tells you the hardest part of moving abroad is not fitting your life into 23kg.\n\nIt is realizing your life was never really inside the things you packed.\n\nAt first, the suitcase feels too small. Too small for the clothes, for the memories\u2026 for the version of you that existed back home.\n\nSo you bring what you can.\nThe gifts. The photos. The little objects that feel like safety. The pieces of home you\u2019re scared to let go of.\n\nBut then you start over.\n\nYou meet people who don\u2019t know your past. You find kindness in strangers. You cry in places no one knows your name. You laugh again in a city that was once unfamiliar.\n\nAnd slowly you understand.\nWhat you miss most was never the stuff. It was the voices. The food. The hugs. The routine. The people who knew you before you had to introduce yourself again.\n\nAfter living in four countries, I learned that what stays with me is not what I packed.\n\nIt is what I felt\u2026\nThe people I met. The strangers who helped me when they didn\u2019t have to. The conversations that changed something in me. The places that made me feel alive again. The love I gave. The love I received\u2764\ufe0f\u200d\ud83e\ude79.\n\nMaybe that\u2019s the move abroad paradox:\n\nyou leave thinking you need to carry your whole life with you, only to realize the most meaningful parts of life were never things you could pack.\n\n#newlife #livingabroad #freshstart #studyabroad #explorar",
